qas.question: The Ranger program from 1959 was managed by what organization?
The first spacecraft to make it to the Moon was what?
The first Ranger mission that didn't fail was which one?
The Block III Ranger 7 mission successfully reached the moon on what date?
What program led to the establishment of the Ranger program?

context: The US reacted to the <a4_0>Luna<a4_0/> program by embarking on the Ranger program in 1959, managed by <a0_0>NASA's Jet Propulsion Laboratory<a0_0/>. The Block I Ranger 1 and Ranger 2 suffered Atlas-Agena launch failures in August and November 1961. The 727-pound (330 kg) Block II Ranger 3 launched successfully on January 26, 1962, but missed the Moon. The 730-pound (330 kg) <a1_0>Ranger 4<a1_0/> became the first US spacecraft to reach the Moon, but its solar panels and navigational system failed near the Moon and it impacted the far side without returning any scientific data. Ranger 5 ran out of power and missed the Moon by 725 kilometers (391 nmi) on October 21, 1962. The first successful Ranger mission was the 806-pound (366 kg) <a2_0>Block III Ranger 7<a2_0/> which impacted on <a3_0>July 31, 1964<a3_0/>.
